If you choose to log in to an LIP-Enabled Service via social media, we may import your friends’ social media user Open ID, nicknames and profile pictures from your social media profile so that you can connect with your friends.
Necessary to perform our contract with you if you request that we connect you with your friends.
Friends list (manually added by you)
If you choose to add a user as a friend, we will store that information so that you can connect with that user.
Necessary to perform our contract with you if you request that we connect you with your friends.
LIP-Enabled Service compliance information:
Open ID, token, region, username, email address. We may also process your parent/legal guardian’s credit card information depending on where you are located.
We use this information to verify your parental or legal guardian consent to allow your child to use LIP-Enabled Services.
We will process this information with the parent’s consent.
Location
: IP address
We use this information to allow you to:
detect any suspicious account activity / logins;
connect to the LIP-Enabled Service server; and
suggest your country/region when you seek to change your location setting.
Necessary to perform our contract with you to provide the LIP-Enabled Service.
It is in our legitimate interest to ensure the security of our services and your account.
