Transactions-related information
Transaction records
: we collect information about your purchases, including payments on Google Play or iOS App Store (Open ID, cost, product purchased, IP address, details of transactions linked to user ID, and device details including OS version, phone model, device root status).
If you make a purchase on a third party platform other than Google Play or iOS App Store, we may also collect your user information (name, username, email address), device information (including Open ID, IP address, OS version, type of device, internet connection), transaction details (time and date, cost, product purchased, currency, order ID) and transaction records (including user ID, time of transaction, country/region, email, phone number, purchase history and payment card details).
We use this information to facilitate your payment and maintain a record of your transaction history.
Necessary to perform our contract with you to facilitate your payment and provide you with details of your transactions.
Transaction identifiers
: unique identifier, name, email address, phone number, country/region code, date of creation of account, number of transactions during different periods, number of top-ups during different periods, number of top-up receivers, number of chargebacks.
We use this information in order to detect fraud in the LIP-Enabled Service.
It is in our legitimate interest to ensure the security of transactions within our services.
Security & Crash solving
Security
: list of installed hack software, equipment brand and model, available space on the device, and information about your internet connection including the type (WiFi/4G/3G).
We use this information to:
provide a fair environment; and
solve crashes and optimize compatibility.
It is in our legitimate interests to use this information to protect the integrity of the LIP-Enabled Service to improve its operation.
Safety observation:
We collect security-related information such as  list of hack or cheating software, in-LIP-Enabled Service screen information, device operation system settings, device information, device identifier, and a list of installed APK and running apps.
If you are using an LIP-Enabled Service running on PC, we may also collect hardware information, operating system information, machine codes for security authentication, user account information, network information, information of files, processes, modules, memory and driver which is related to the LIP-Enabled Service running, user behaviour and status that may be related to plug-in use or sale of plug-ins through profile pictures, image files, memory image and shellcode which is related to the LIP-Enabled Service running, system API calls, method calls, system procedures and related data of active windows, information on in-LIP-Enabled Service modules, LIP-Enabled Service screenshots, external programs attempting to access private data which belongs to process of LIP-Enabled Service application.
We use this information:
for security and verification purposes, including to detect and observe cheating behaviours and consider restricting or banning access to the LIP-Enabled Service;
to identify and address bugs and assess LIP-Enabled Service function for optimisation;
to solve LIP-Enabled Service crashes and optimise compatibility of devices with the LIP-Enabled Service; and
to combat users registering for multiple accounts.
If your LIP Account is determined to breach our Terms of Service, we may consider restricting or banning your access to the LIP-Enabled Service.
It Is in our legitimate interest to ensure the security of our services, to maintain a fair gaming environment in the LIP-Enabled Service and to manage registrations and improve our services.
Crash resolving
: information relating to the device you use to use our LIP-Enabled Service, such as device model, brand and operating system.
We use this information for locating and solving crash issues.
It is in our legitimate interest to ensure the security and integrity of our LIP-Enabled Service.
